<![CDATA[<p>Newer phones come with WAP2 which uses HTML Mobile Profile (XHTML MP), which is quite similar to normal HTML.  Older phones use Wireless Markup Language (WML). </p><br/><br/><p>Depending on your audience I would consider making a mobile phone friendly version of the site using XHTML MP and drop WML completely. By mobile phone friendly I mean light graphics, little JavaScript and simple navigation.</p><br/><br/><p>To check capabilities of different hand phones, take look at <a href="http://wurfl.sourceforge.net/" rel="nofollow" title="Wireless Universal Resource File">WURFL</a>.</p><br/><br/><p>Also, you might want to take a look at <a href="http://www.w3.org/TR/2008/REC-mobile-bp-20080729/" rel="nofollow" title="Mobile Web Best Practices">Mobile Web Best Practices</a> from w3c.</p><br/>]]>    </template>
