    </pattern>
    <template>
<![CDATA[<p>This is the solution I have working in Firefox 3, Opera and Google Chrome. The list still displays in IE7 (but without the close bracket and left align numbers):</p><br/><br/><pre><code>&lt;style type="text/css"&gt;<br/>&lt;!--<br/>ol {<br/>    counter-reset: item;<br/>    margin-left: 0;<br/>    padding-left: 0;<br/>}<br/>li {<br/>    display: block;<br/>    margin-bottom: .5em;<br/>    margin-left: 2em;<br/>}<br/>li:before {<br/>    display: inline-block;<br/>    content: counter(item) ") ";<br/>    counter-increment: item;<br/>    width: 2em;<br/>    margin-left: -2em;<br/>}<br/>--&gt;<br/>&lt;/style&gt;<br/>&lt;body&gt;<br/>&lt;ol&gt;<br/>  &lt;li&gt;One&lt;/li&gt;<br/>  &lt;li&gt;Two&lt;/li&gt;<br/>  &lt;li&gt;Three&lt;/li&gt;<br/>  &lt;li&gt;Four&lt;/li&gt;<br/>  &lt;li&gt;Five&lt;/li&gt;<br/>  &lt;li&gt;Six&lt;/li&gt;<br/>  &lt;li&gt;Seven&lt;/li&gt;<br/>  &lt;li&gt;Eight&lt;/li&gt;<br/>  &lt;li&gt;Nine&lt;br&gt;Items&lt;/li&gt;<br/>  &lt;li&gt;Ten&lt;br&gt;Items&lt;/li&gt;<br/>&lt;/ol&gt;<br/></code></pre><br/><br/><p><strong>EDIT:</strong> Included multiple line fix by strager</p><br/><br/><blockquote><br/>  <p>Also is there a CSS solution to change from numbers to alphabetic/roman lists instead of using the type attribute on the ol element.</p><br/></blockquote><br/><br/><p>Refer to <a href="http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS2/generate.html#lists" rel="nofollow">list-style-type</a> CSS property. Or when using counters the second argument accepts a list-style-type value. For example the following will use upper roman:</p><br/><br/><pre><code>li:before {<br/>    content: counter(item, upper-roman) ") ";<br/>    counter-increment: item;<br/>/* ... */<br/></code></pre><br/>]]>    </template>
