    <template>
<![CDATA[<p>I know you mentioned that you don't want to, but I actually think that using the <code>disabled</code> attribute is a better solution:</p><br/><br/><pre><code>&lt;select multiple="multiple"&gt;<br/>    &lt;option value="volvo" selected="true" disabled="disabled"&gt;Volvo&lt;/option&gt;<br/>    &lt;option value="saab" disabled="disabled"&gt;Saab&lt;/option&gt;<br/>    &lt;option value="opel" disabled="disabled"&gt;Opel&lt;/option&gt;<br/>    &lt;option value="audi" disabled="disabled"&gt;Audi&lt;/option&gt;<br/>&lt;/select&gt;<br/></code></pre><br/><br/><p>If necessary, you can always give the <code>select</code> a <code>class</code> and style it with CSS. This solution will work in all browsers regardless of scripting capabilities.</p><br/>]]>    </template>
